    "title": "getchaintips doesn't mark headers-only chain as invalid",
    "body": "During headers-first downloading, if an invalid block is found, the client stops syncing that branch, but forever lists it as \"headers-only\". It seems to me it should be marked as \"invalid\". This is due to the subsequent headers not being marked \"BLOCK_FAILED_CHILD\".\n",
